This paper deals with the problem of generating textual paraphrases, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also proposes new loss functions and training strategies, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation metrics for the generated paraphrases, which involves measuring semantic content preservation and fluency, both of which are important in information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
